HEADWORD: Havier
<hw>Hav"ier</hw> <pr>(h⟦amac⟧"y⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Formerly <ets>haver</ets>, prob. fr. <er>Half</er>; cf. L.
<ets>semimas</ets> emasculated, prop., half male.]</ety> <def>A
castrated deer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Haviers</qex>, or stags which have been gelded when young,
have no horns.</q> <rj><qau>Encyc. of Sport.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

